  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Lamentations 3:31-33",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Lamentations 3:31-33",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Lord will not cast off for ever ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— The truly penitent that put their trust in him, and sincerely desire and seek reconciliation with him: though he may for a time appear to estrange himself from them, yet he will certainly return to them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Though he cause grief — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Though, as a prudent parent, he may see reason to chastise his people by affliction, yet as a kind and tender Father, who pitieth his children in misery, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "according to the multitude, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the unspeakable greatness and abundance of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "his mercies, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he will have compassion upon them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For he doth not afflict willingly — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "מלבו",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "from his heart, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, of his own mere motion, without cause given him by the persons afflicted; or freely and with pleasure; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "nor grieve the children of men — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Much less his own children. Hence judgment is called his ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "strange work, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and exercising mercy and loving-kindness his delight.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
