        "text": "Psalm 123:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. There is a certain gradation in the three verses that it quite unmistakeable. The sitting alone and in silence is comparatively the easiest; it is harder to place the mouth in the dust, and yet cling to hope; it is most difficult of all to give the cheek to the smiter, and to satiate oneself with dishonour (Ngelsbach). In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
